<dl id="n42026c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42026c">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42026c"> 26(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> penitentiary</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The office of the penitentiary was this: In every large city, a priest or minister was specially appointed to preside over the church meetings, where the members who had committed public sins were obliged to confess them publicly before the assembly, in order to be reinstated in the privileges of their membership; <small> Chiniquy, <a name="CPWC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CPWC"><cite title="source">The Priest The Woman and The Confessional</cite></a> (n.d.) 127</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
